------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party software
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Design Factory depends on a number of open-source packages distributed
under their own licenses. The composite dependency tree is dominated
by MIT, Apache-2.0, ISC, and BSD-3-Clause. The `package.json` manifest
and the `package-lock.json` resolution are the authoritative record of
each dependency, its version, and its licence at install time.

To enumerate every dependency licence after `npm install`:

    find node_modules -maxdepth 2 -name package.json | \
      xargs -I{} node -e "const p=require('./{}'); \
        console.log((p.name||'?')+'@'+(p.version||'?')+' '+\
          (p.license||p.licenses||'UNKNOWN'))"

No copyleft (AGPL, LGPL, SSPL, GPL-2, GPL-3) dependency is currently
present in the resolved tree. Re-check dependency licenses before every
`v*.0.0` tag.

